<div style="padding:8px 32px; font-size:16px; line-height:1.4; background-color:white; color:#F44;">
    <h3 style="font-size:36px; font-weight:normal;">You must have <strong>PHP v5.3.1</strong> or later to use SilverWp framework.</h3>
    <p>You can try adding the following to the top of your <code>.htaccess</code> file in the WordPress root directory:</p>
    <p><code style="background:#f4f4f4; border:1px solid #ddd; padding:7px 14px; color:#222; font-size:14px; ">AddType application/x-httpd-php53 .php</code></p>
    <p style="margin-top:3em;">If that does not work, contact your host and ask him/her to update your PHP version. The theme will not be functional until this issue is corrected.</p>
</div>